Function Reference/status header « WordPress Codex
-----------

Set HTTP status header.

Usage
-----

` <?php status_header( $header ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$header` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) [HTTP status
    code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes "wikipedia:List of HTTP status codes")
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (null) 
:   Does not return anything.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    Calls '`status_header`' on status header string, HTTP HTTP code,
    HTTP code description, and protocol string as separate parameters.

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.0.0

Source File
-----------

`status_header()` is located in `wp-includes/functions.php`.

